                <p>Not all characteristics can be passed to the next generation.</p>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>Inherited Traits <span class="punjabi">(ਜੱਦੀ ਲੱਛਣ)</span></th><th>Acquired Traits <span class="punjabi">(ਗ੍ਰਹਿਣ ਕੀਤੇ ਲੱਛਣ)</span></th></tr>
                    <tr><td>Passed down from parents through DNA.</td><td>Developed during a lifetime due to environment.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Causes changes in the <span class="exam-keyword" title="Sperm or Egg">Germ cells</span>.</td><td>Only affects <span class="exam-keyword" title="Body cells">Somatic cells</span>. DNA is not changed.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td><em>Example:</em> Eye color, blood group.</td><td><em>Example:</em> Learning to swim, a scar, or cutting a mouse's tail.</td></tr>
