                <div class="sequencer-container" id="seq-ch8-1">
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>1. The Base:</strong> Humans have 23 pairs of chromosomes. The 23rd pair are the sex chromosomes. Females are <span class="exam-keyword">XX</span>, Males are <span class="exam-keyword">XY</span>.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>2. Gametes (Mothers):</strong> During egg formation, pairs separate. The mother produces eggs that <strong>ALL</strong> carry the X chromosome (100% X).
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>3. Gametes (Fathers):</strong> The father produces sperm where <strong>50% carry X</strong> and <strong>50% carry Y</strong>.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>4. Fertilization:</strong> If an X-sperm fertilizes the egg &rarr; Girl (XX). If a Y-sperm fertilizes the egg &rarr; Boy (XY).
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <span class="accent-blue">Conclusion:</span> The mother always gives an X. The sex of the child is determined entirely by what the <strong>father</strong> contributes!
                    </div>
