        <div class="slide">
            <div class="content-box">
                <h2>Decoding Magnification ($m$) <span class="punjabi">(ਵੱਡਦਰਸ਼ਣ)</span></h2>
                <p>Magnification tells you the height of the image compared to the object. It reveals the exact nature of the image instantly.</p>
                <div class="equation">m = h' / h = -v / u</div>
                
                <h3 style="margin-top: 15px;">Rule 1: The Sign (+ or -)</h3>
                <ul style="background: #F8FAFC; padding: 15px 15px 15px 40px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <li>If $m$ is <span class="accent-blue">Negative (-)</span> &rarr; Image is <strong>Real and Inverted</strong>.</li>
                    <li>If $m$ is <span class="accent-blue">Positive (+)</span> &rarr; Image is <strong>Virtual and Erect</strong>.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 style="margin-top: 15px;">Rule 2: The Number Value</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>If $|m| > 1$ (e.g., 2, -3): Image is Enlarged (Magnified).</li>
                    <li>If $|m| < 1$ (e.g., 0.5, -0.2): Image is Diminished (Smaller).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

