                    <strong>Optical Density Rule:</strong> A higher index (like diamond's 2.42) means the medium is more optically dense. This means light travels <span class="cloze-blank" data-hint="S..." data-ans="Slower" onclick="revealCloze(this)"></span>, and the ray of light bends <span class="cloze-blank" data-hint="T..." data-ans="Towards" onclick="revealCloze(this)"></span> the normal line.
