        <div class="slide">
            <div class="content-box">
                <h2>1. Oersted's Experiment</h2>
                <p>Hans Christian Oersted discovered that a compass needle deflects near a current-carrying wire, proving that <strong>electricity creates magnetism</strong>.</p>
                
                <h3 style="margin-top:20px;">Properties of Field Lines (3-Mark Rule)</h3>
                <ol style="background: #F8FAFC; padding: 20px 20px 20px 40px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
                    <li>Field lines emerge from <strong>North</strong> and merge at <strong>South</strong> (outside).</li>
                    <li>Inside the magnet, direction is South to North (forming closed loops).</li>
                    <li>The relative strength is shown by the closeness of the lines.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SPOT THE ERROR -->
        <div class="slide">
            <div class="content-box">
                <h2>Spot-the-Error Inspector <span class="punjabi">(ਗਲਤੀ ਲੱਭੋ)</span></h2>
                <p><strong>Task:</strong> Find the critical physics error in this diagram representation and tap it to fix it.</p>
                
                <div class="error-diagram">
                    <div style="font-weight: bold; color: var(--goku-primary);">[ NORTH POLE ] . . . . . . . . . . [ SOUTH POLE ]</div>
                    <br>
                    Field Line A: <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--goku-primary); width: 100px;"></span> &rarr;
                    <br><br>
                    Field Line B: <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--goku-primary); width: 40px; transform: rotate(20deg);"></span> 
                    <span class="hotspot" onclick="fixError(this, 'error-exp-1')">INTERSECTS</span> 
                    <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--goku-primary); width: 40px; transform: rotate(-20deg);"></span> Line A
                </div>
                
                <div class="error-explanation" id="error-exp-1">
                    <strong>CORRECTED!</strong> Magnetic field lines CANNOT intersect. If they did, it would mean the magnetic force is pulling in two different directions at the exact same point, which is physically impossible.
