                <h2>5. Domestic Safety Hazards <span class="punjabi">(ਘਰੇਲੂ ਸੁਰੱਖਿਆ ਖ਼ਤਰੇ)</span></h2>
                <p>Homes receive AC power at 220V. You must clearly differentiate the two main electrical hazards:</p>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>Short Circuiting <span class="punjabi">(ਸ਼ਾਰਟ ਸਰਕਟ)</span></th><th>Overloading <span class="punjabi">(ਓਵਰਲੋਡਿੰਗ)</span></th></tr>
                    <tr><td>Happens if plastic insulation melts and the <strong>Live wire touches the Neutral wire</strong> directly.</td><td>Happens when <strong>too many high-power appliances</strong> are plugged into a single socket.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Resistance drops to almost zero, causing a massive, immediate current spike and potential fire.</td><td>The total current drawn exceeds the capacity of the wires, slowly overheating them.</td></tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

