                <h2>2. Biological Magnification <span class="board-badge">🏆 Process Flow</span></h2>
                <p><strong>Interactive Sequencer:</strong> Build the DDT toxin accumulation chain. Notice how the concentration increases at every step.</p>
                <div class="sequencer-container" id="seq-ch13-1">
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>1. Water Source:</strong> Farmers spray pesticides (DDT). It washes into a local pond at a very low, safe concentration.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>2. Producers (Plankton):</strong> Microscopic plants absorb the DDT. They cannot excrete it.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>3. Primary Consumers (Small Fish):</strong> Eat hundreds of plankton. The DDT accumulates heavily in their fat.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>4. Secondary Consumers (Large Fish):</strong> Eat dozens of small fish. Concentration spikes dramatically.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>5. Top Carnivores (Humans/Birds):</strong> We eat the large fish and receive the <span class="exam-keyword">maximum toxic dose</span>, leading to severe diseases.
                    </div>
                    <button class="seq-btn" onclick="revealNextStep('seq-ch13-1')">
                        Reveal Next Trophic Level <span class="seq-counter">[0/5]</span>
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide">
            <div class="content-box">
                <h2>3. Ozone Formation & Depletion</h2>
                <p>Ozone (O₃) forms a protective shield in the upper atmosphere against UV radiation.</p>
                
                <div class="equation" style="display:block; text-align:center; padding: 15px;">
                    1. &nbsp; O<sub>2</sub> &nbsp; &#x2192; (UV Light) &rarr; &nbsp; O + O <br><br>
                    2. &nbsp; O + O<sub>2</sub> &nbsp; &#x2192; &nbsp; O<sub>3</sub> (Ozone)
                </div>
                
                <p>It is destroyed by <span class="exam-keyword">CFCs</span> (Chlorofluorocarbons) used in old refrigerators, causing the "Ozone Hole".</p>
            </div>
        </div>

